Vodacom has stated that the company has not raised its contract tariffs, following questions from MyBroadband. The questions arose after MyBroadband readers pointed out what appeared to be price hikes for certain Samsung smartphone contracts. Two of the examples provided were: Vodacom told MyBroadband that it has not increased its contract tariffs, and that “pricing on deals and promotions differ and change from time to time”. “Please note that the two examples you mentioned are deal specific. Pricing on deals and promotions change from time to time, depending on the packages or bundles we structure for that specific month,” said Vodacom.